We bumped pybind11 in 2025.3.2.0, so you need to bump all of your robotpy packages and vendor packages to the latest version to be compatible.

You need to have robotpy-playingwithfusion 2025.1.23.1.

RobotPy 2025.3.2.0 available Python
Bumped to latest WPILib release, and also updated all of the versions for all supported vendors. A big change here is we upgraded to the latest beta release of pybind11, so none of the updated wheels will be compatible with older wheels. This will resolve some issues we’ve had with MSVC and non-ubuntu Linux platforms. There are some changes to the type stubs as a result of this update, so if you’re using mypy et al then you may notice some breakage. Please try this out and let us know if there…
